⊕meta⊕
name = "post-slack"
description = "Post a plain-text message to Slack via an incoming webhook URL held in a named env var. Invoke from orchestration workflows or run manually. Fire via: skyway run post-slack --var webhook_env_name=SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL --var text=<message>"
params.webhook_env_name.type = "string"
params.webhook_env_name.required = true
params.webhook_env_name.description = "Name of the env var holding the Slack incoming webhook URL."
params.text.type = "string"
params.text.required = true
params.text.description = "Plain-text message body."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
ui = "ui/workflow"
⊕⊕

※post※
Bash root node. Resolves the webhook URL indirectly from webhook_env_name, builds JSON with jq -n, and POSTs to Slack. No retry (sink).
※※

§post§
bash = ": \"${SKY_WEBHOOK_ENV_NAME:?webhook_env_name required}\"; : \"${SKY_TEXT:?text required}\"; url_var=\"$SKY_WEBHOOK_ENV_NAME\"; : \"${!url_var:?${url_var} not set}\"; jq -n --arg text \"$SKY_TEXT\" '{text:$text}' | curl -sS --fail --max-time 30 -X POST -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- \"${!url_var}\""
ui = "ui/post"
§§

※※
post-slack — deterministic Slack webhook sink micro-workflow

One pure-bash node, no LLM cost, no retry.

Resolves the webhook URL from an env var named by webhook_env_name (indirect
expansion), builds JSON with jq -n, and POSTs with curl --fail --max-time 30.

Invoke from orchestration:
  invoke = { target = "post-slack", vars = { webhook_env_name = "SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL", text = "..." } }

Run manually:
  skyway run post-slack --var webhook_env_name=SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL --var text="Shipped"

Vars:
  webhook_env_name  env var name holding the webhook URL  -> $SKY_WEBHOOK_ENV_NAME
  text              plain-text message                    -> $SKY_TEXT
※※